.TH "lpfcdiag_loop_post_rxbufs" 9 "lpfcdiag_loop_post_rxbufs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfcdiag_loop_post_rxbufs \- post the receive buffers for an unsol CT cmd
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfcdiag_loop_post_rxbufs
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "uint16_t rxxri "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
Pointer to HBA context object
.IP "rxxri" 12
Receive exchange id
.IP "len" 12
Number of data bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates and posts a data buffer of sufficient size to receive
an unsolicted CT command.
